   537→**Update server.py for Windows audio:**
   538→
   539→```python
   540→import platform
   541→import subprocess
   542→import os
   543→
   544→def play_audio(audio_file: str):
   545→    """Play audio file on Windows, Mac, or Linux"""
   546→    system = platform.system()
   547→
   548→    if system == "Windows":
   549→        # Windows: use powershell with media player
   550→        cmd = [
   551→            "powershell",
   552→            "-Command",
   553→            f"(New-Object Media.SoundPlayer '{audio_file}').PlaySync()"
   554→        ]
   555→        subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True)
   556→    elif system == "Darwin":
   557→        # macOS: afplay
   558→        subprocess.run(["afplay", audio_file])
   559→    else:
   560→        # Linux: paplay (PulseAudio) or aplay (ALSA)
   561→        try:
   562→            subprocess.run(["paplay", audio_file], check=False)
   563→        except FileNotFoundError:
   564→            subprocess.run(["aplay", audio_file], check=False)
   565→```
